Theo Walcott believes the Arsenal forward line could turn out to be the best in the club's history - but they must prove exactly how good they are by winning plenty of silverware.

The 25-year-old, who missed the vast majority of 2014 through injury, believes the current crop - which includes Alexis Sanchez, Olivier Giroud, Santi Cazorla and Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain - can top that of the Invincibles' line-up which included most notably Thierry Henry and Dennis Bergkamp.

Walcott told Arsenal player: 'When I came here, it was Robert Pires and Freddie Ljungberg, Bergkamp, Thierry and Jose Reyes - that's some attacking force as well.  

