He added: 'You see somebody working so hard and it makes you want to try to back him up.

'When you see what he does off the pitch, behind the scenes at the training ground, and how much work he puts in, all the players just stand up and think: Yeah, I need to do a bit more as well then.'

Next up for the Gunners is a trip to Brighton in the FA Cup fourth round on Sunday, before returning to Premier League action at home to Aston Villa the following week. 

